    "answer_id" : 61791308,
    "question_id" : 11219556,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>This is just a convention or a practice people follow to keep coding style consistent. It improves the readability.\nso preferred way of writing this is</p>\n\n<pre><code>private static final &lt;Type&gt; &lt;variable_name&gt; = &lt;value&gt;;\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 17333464,
      "reputation" : 121,
      "user_id" : 12555956,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/f6f0feedbc359b22127687e7c154e161?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "RRK",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/12555956/rrk"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 12,
    "last_activity_date" : 1631594204,
    "creation_date" : 1631594204,
    "answer_id" : 69171852,
    "question_id" : 11219556,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p><strong>No difference logically and no technical impact.</strong></p>\n<p>only issue is that sonarqube will report Code Smell if you use in this order</p>\n<pre><code>private final static &lt;Type&gt; &lt;variable_name&gt; = &lt;value&gt;;\n</code></pre>\n<p>Hence recommendation is to use :</p>\n<pre><code>private static final &lt;Type&gt; &lt;variable_name&gt; = &lt;value&gt;;\n</code></pre>\n<p>The Java Language Specification recommends listing modifiers in the following order:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Annotations</li>\n<li>public</li>\n<li>protected</li>\n<li>private</li>\n<li>abstract</li>\n<li>static</li>\n<li>final</li>\n<li>transient</li>\n<li>volatile</li>\n<li>synchronized</li>\n<li>native</li>\n<li>strictfp</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Note following this convention has no technical impact, but will reduce the code's readability because most developers are used to the standard order.</p>\n"
  } ],
